node.text:
Marine Harvest is perfect for anyone who enjoys delicious and convenient seafood! Products are high quality, healthy, and affordable foods to bring into your home. They are also perfect for busy parents who prefer homemade meals that are better than fast food for their kids. I used their Atlantic Salmon Poppers to make this Dynamite Salmon Poppers. Makes life a whole lot easier. They are available at @target Superstores and soon on @amazonfresh.

#MarineHarvest #MOWI #YummyFish #FishBites #Target #AmazonFresh

🔹DYNAMITE SAUCE🔹

1/2 cup mayo (or light mayo, can reduce to 1/3 cup)
1/2 cup sweet & chili sauce
1 tsp vinegar
2 tbsps ketchup
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tbsp honey
3 tbsps sriracha sauce

node.title: Make meal time exciting with @marineharvest_usa frozen fish line

node.text:
This 5 ingredient Crispy Chicken Bites recipe is the easiest and most convenient summer snack/finger food recipe for kids and even adults! Because it’s made with the @ThePioneerWoman’s Anything Goes Seasoning, you will not need any extra spices to pull this recipe. It is made with an all purpose blend of coarse sea salt, celery, black pepper, onion and garlic kissed with a burst of lemon zest. Great for brightening up chicken. I am so happy that @Kroger is carrying these seasonings now! Believe me – get them!

These chicken bites are so crispy, juicy and tender, they will be your #1 go to recipe when you need something quick and easy to make.

Ingredients

•  1 lb. chicken tenderloin cubed into 1" bites
 * ¾ cup flour, for dredging
•  1 ½ tbsps. seasoning of choice I used The Pioneer Women Anything Goes Seasoning
•  1 whole egg
* 2 tbsps. heavy cream 
* canola oil for frying

Instructions

Cut chicken into 1" cubes. Set aside in a bowl.
In a shallow bowl/plate, mix together the flour and seasoning. In another bowl, whisk the egg and heavy cream together. * Dip a piece of chicken into the flour mixture, then the egg mixture and then back again into the flour mixture, patting the flour well into the chicken.
Set the piece of chicken aside on a sheet pan and continue repeating the process for the remainder of the chicken pieces.
Fill a deep skillet with about 2-3" of canola oil and bring to medium heat, around 350 F. * Deep fry the chicken cubes for about 5 minutes, until crispy brown and fully cooked on the inside. Do 2 batches to prevent overcrowding.
Remove the chicken from the oil and set for a couple of minutes on a paper towel to drain any excess oil. * Transfer to a plate and serve with your favorite sauce.

https://www.cookinwithmima.com/crispy-chicken-bites/

Set the piece of chicken aside on a sheet pan and continue repeating the process for the remainder of the chicken pieces.
Fill a deep skillet with about 2-3" of canola oil and bring to medium heat, around 350 F. * Deep fry the chicken cubes for about 5 minutes, until crispy brown and fully cooked on the inside. Do 2 batches to prevent overcrowding.
Remove the chicken from the oil and set for a couple of minutes on a paper towel to drain any excess oil. * Transfer to a plate and serve with your favorite sauce.
